subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Total length (head + trunk) of the holotype 3.9 mm. Habitus typically of paronellids (
Fig. 1
). Specimen with dark purple color covering posteriorly to eyepatches, margin of Th II, Abd III with one transversal band and abdomen IV with one on central region; coxa I–II, femur III, and all tibiotarsi distally. Bluish brown irregular pigment covering antennas, head and legs (
Fig. 1
). Body covered by different types of chaetae, sens, bothriotricha and scales (
Figs 2–7
). Hyaline, denticulate, apically rounded or truncate scales covering the Ant I–II, both faces of head, thorax, abdomen, legs, posterior face of the collophore, both faces of manubrium and anteriorly dens (
Figs 6
,
26 and 30
).

